abstract: The Chinese Internet search firm Baidu.com is pondering acquisitions and possibly a Hong Kong share listing to fuel an expansion into the country’s consumer Internet market, taking on Alibaba.com in the world’s second-largest Web market.
lead_paragraph: The Chinese Internet search firm Baidu.com is pondering acquisitions and possibly a Hong Kong share listing to fuel an expansion into the country’s consumer Internet market, taking on Alibaba.com in the world’s second-largest Web market.

headline.main: After Alibaba, Baidu Considers I.P.O. of Its Own
